values.content:
=Synthesize this enrichment data into a prospect brief.

## Lead
Name: {{ $('When Executed by Parent').item.json.first_name }} {{ $('When Executed by Parent').item.json.last_name }}
Title: {{ $('When Executed by Parent').item.json.title }}
Company: {{ $('When Executed by Parent').item.json.company_name }}
Fit score: {{ $('When Executed by Parent').item.json.fit_score }} (Tier {{ $('When Executed by Parent').item.json.tier }})
Pain hypothesis: {{ $('When Executed by Parent').item.json.pain_hypothesis }}

## Website HTML (truncate to first 4000 chars)
{{ ($('🌐 Fetch Company Website').item.json.data || '').toString().substring(0,4000) }}

## LinkedIn JSON
{{ JSON.stringify($('🔗 Fetch LinkedIn Profile').item.json).substring(0,3000) }}

## Recent News JSON
{{ JSON.stringify(($('📰 Fetch Recent News').item.json && $('📰 Fetch Recent News').item.json.news_results) || []).substring(0,2000) }}

Return JSON in this EXACT schema:
{
  "company_one_liner": "<what the company actually does, 1 sentence>",
  "company_recent_signal": "<most relevant trigger from news/site, or 'unknown'>",
  "prospect_role_summary": "<what this person likely owns at the company>",
  "prospect_observable_pain": "<specific pipeline/outbound pain inferred from role + company stage>",
  "relevance_to_dropmeds": "<one sentence connecting their pain to DropMeds value>",
  "confidence": "high" | "medium" | "low"
}

parameters.jsCode:
const lead = $('When Executed by Parent').item.json;
let brief = $input.first().json;
if (brief && brief.message && brief.message.content) {
  try { brief = typeof brief.message.content === 'string' ? JSON.parse(brief.message.content) : brief.message.content; } catch(e) {
    brief = { company_one_liner:'unknown', company_recent_signal:'unknown', prospect_role_summary:'unknown', prospect_observable_pain:'unknown', relevance_to_dropmeds:'unknown', confidence:'low' };
  }
}
return [{ json: { ...lead, prospect_brief: brief } }];
